JOHANNESBURG - For the second day in a row, South Africa has recorded over 5,000 coronavirus infections. These take our known caseload since the start of the pandemic to 1,680,000. Today the cumulative number of #COVID19 cases identified in South Africa is 1 680 373. Today, 54 COVID-19 related deaths have been reported which brings the total to 56 765 deaths.Our recoveries now stand at 1 567 635, representing a recovery rate of 93,3% pic.twitter.com/mWufOtNKii  03 June 2021 #COVID19 statistics in South Africa #CoronaVirusSA pic.twitter.com/QbkjgzSV4E  Sadly, 54 more people have died in this country after contracting the virus, with the death toll now at 56,765. On the recovery front, 1,567,000 people have recuperated which translates to a rate of 93.3%. The Health Department said that just over 1, 193,000 healthcare workers and people over the age of 60 had now had at least one shot of a COVID-19 vaccination. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.